    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, ITreeNode<NODETYPE>, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<NODETYPE>>
    public class ProductCategoryTreeNode<NODETYPE>
extends CategoryTreeNode<NODETYPE,​ProductCategory>
    This class represents a product category in an ITree and extends the CategoryTreeNode class. It binds the typeparameter CATEGORY of CategoryTreeNode to ProductCategory. This means that the ProductCategoryTreeNode only allows values of the Enum ProductCategory as categories.

      • deepCopy

        public ProductCategoryTreeNode<NODETYPE> deepCopy()
        Description copied from class: GenericTreeNode
        Creates a copy of the GenericTreeNode and all its attributes and returns it. All attributes that implement the IDeepCopy interface have to be copied via the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method as well. This means that also all direct child ITreeNodes which implement the IDeepCopy interface have to be copied via the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method.

        Redefined here to limit the return type of the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method to ITreeNode.

        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 

         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.
